<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=500&amp;p=3879#p3879"><![CDATA[
My Advice:<br /><br />- Write the CPU core first<br />- Start with basic roms (no mapper) and no scrolling games (popeye, king kong, etc)<br />- When you see a crash in the cpu, fix it<br />- Make a simple ppu engine (just to show the screen)<br />- Its not a bad idea to emulate input, so you can run nestress and check your cpu core.<br />- dont worry at first for IRQ, worry about NMI<br />- if you want to run it in WIN32. Use directdraw for output, GDI is slower<br />- Ask in this forum if you have a problem.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=72">Anes</a> — Thu Aug 18, 2005 3:02 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
