<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=500&amp;p=3839#p3839"><![CDATA[
I wrote a simple (unreleased) NES emulator a while back and it was fun. I intentionally wrote it very simply so it only plays a few MMC1 games and doesn't even handle a fixed status display at the top (it scrolls with the main screen). It was a good learning experience and I still occasionally experiment with features. If you want new ideas, you could focus on specializing it for a particular game then adding extensions, like graphics with more colors.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Wed Aug 17, 2005 9:00 am</p><hr />
